<paragraph blockId="36.[178,1085,1407,1516]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
Black. Pale yellow: the whole of clypeus but semitransparent ventral edge; subapical 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[178,217,1436,1458]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">Tsa</emphasis>
; apical palpi; two lateral subapical stripes on 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[707,733,1436,1460]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
N 
<subScript attach="left" box="[725,733,1446,1460]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
disk; half tegula; most of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1018,1078,1436,1460]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
LaSt 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1070,1078,1446,1460]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
; ventral surface of coxae, tarsi and most of legs; narrow apical stripe on 1st to 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1006,1018,1459,1473]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">th</superScript>
terga; two lateral apical stripes on 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[475,491,1489,1503]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">nd</superScript>
to 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[536,548,1489,1503]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">th</superScript>
sterna. Wings hyaline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[178,1085,1532,1585]" lastBlockId="37.[178,1086,213,387]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="1694" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[178,226,1532,1554]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">PoG</emphasis>
about half 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[347,395,1532,1554]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">FoO</emphasis>
. Mid flagellomeri with a ratio 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,739,1532,1554]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">L</emphasis>
/ 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[746,781,1532,1554]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">LA</emphasis>
mor than 2.4. No keel along fore border neither tooth on antero ventral corner of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[727,753,1561,1585]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
N 
<subScript attach="left" box="[745,753,1571,1585]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
disk. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[818,864,1561,1585]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
Em 
<subScript attach="left" box="[856,864,1571,1585]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">3</subScript>
</emphasis>
with strong wrinkles along the 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[279,331,218,240]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">smm</emphasis>
. Hind femur with a distinct ventral longitudinal lamella apically. 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1015,1026,213,227]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">st</superScript>
to 5 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1073,1085,213,227]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">th</superScript>
tergal surfaes bipunctate by sparse large 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[612,626,248,270]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">p</emphasis>
among very small 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,849,248,270]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">p</emphasis>
. Epipygium short and prominent upon the remainder of 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[554,566,271,285]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">th</superScript>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[578,606,277,299]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">Te</emphasis>
with very shallow median notch. Very long dense hair (longer than mid flagellomeri) on most of head and mesosoma, covering underlying integument on clypeus, frons, pronotal disk, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[746,781,336,360]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">
Es 
<subScript attach="left" box="[773,781,346,360]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,829,336,360]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">
Es 
<subScript attach="left" box="[821,829,346,360]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[878,893,336,358]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">P</emphasis>
. Long hair also on tergal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[178,1086,402,453]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">N o t e. Distinct by the dense long hair on head and mesosoma and very narrow gonosquama.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[178,1085,469,520]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">Derivatio nominis. From the Greek words ȑȡȚȠȞ = wool and ıȫμĮ = body because of the dense hair on the head and mesosoma.</paragraph>
